[2026-07-19T12:31:25.733Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"glob@10 deprecated npm warn \"versions prior to v11\" izs\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"🐛 Bug: Mocha 11.7.5 depends on deprecated/vulnerable version of glob (v10.5.0) · Issue #5779 · mochajs/mocha\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/issues/5779\"},{\"title\":\"Deprecated glob@10.5.0 warning during npm install (via rimraf) · Issue #18327 · google-gemini/gemini-cli\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/18327\"},{\"title\":\"Issues Deploying React Builds - Railway Help Station\",\"url\":\"https://station.railway.com/questions/issues-deploying-react-builds-17f4138a\"},{\"title\":\"npm warn deprecated glob@8.1.0: Glob versions prior to v9 are no longer supported · Issue #7029 · netlify/cli\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/netlify/cli/issues/7029\"},{\"title\":\"npm : npm warn deprecated glob@7.2.3: Glob versions prior to v9 are no longer supported - Forge - The Atlassian Developer Community\",\"url\":\"https://community.developer.atlassian.com/t/npm-npm-warn-deprecated-glob-7-2-3-glob-versions-prior-to-v9-are-no-longer-supported/80773\"},{\"title\":\"[Bug]: jest-transform uses a deprecated version of the glob package · Issue #15853 · jestjs/jest\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jestjs/jest/issues/15853\"},{\"title\":\"npm install still emits deprecated glob@10.5.0 via gaxios@7.1.3 · Issue #2 · gsd-build/gsd-2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gsd-build/gsd-2/issues/2\"},{\"title\":\"[Bug]: Please update dependencies to fix deprecation warnings (glob, node-domexception) · Issue #47721 · openclaw/openclaw\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/47721\"},{\"title\":\"Deprecation warning during update - Friends of the ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1482336931453866085\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the `glob@10` deprecation warning:\n\nThe npm warning states: \"Old versions of glob are not supported, and contain widely publicized security vulnerabilities, which have been fixed in the current version.\"\n\nThe deprecation warning is being triggered across various projects that have `glob` version 10 or earlier as transitive dependencies. The dependency chain often shows it coming from packages like rimraf via gaxios.\n\nThe deprecation message includes contact information: \"Support for old versions may be purchased (at exorbitant rates) by contacting i@izs.me\" — where \"izs\" refers to the npm glob package maintainer.\n\nThe solution generally involves updating dependencies that rely on older versions of glob to use versions 9 or higher, or updating the packages that depend on glob to versions that use the latest glob.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
