[2026-07-19T12:31:27.038Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"npm warn deprecated CI suppress loglevel transitive dependencies best practice\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Fix: npm WARN deprecated inflight, glob, rimraf, and Other Package Warnings - FixDevs\",\"url\":\"https://fixdevs.com/blog/npm-warn-deprecated/\"},{\"title\":\"How to handle npm WARN deprecated messages when installing dependencies | sebhastian\",\"url\":\"https://sebhastian.com/npm-warn-deprecated/\"},{\"title\":\"npm WARN deprecated package — How to Fix\",\"url\":\"https://generalistprogrammer.com/errors/npm-warn-deprecated-package\"},{\"title\":\"How to handle npm warn deprecated messages when installing dependencies\",\"url\":\"https://codegive.com/blog/how_to_handle_npm_warn_deprecated_messages_when_installing_dependencies.php\"},{\"title\":\"[BUG] Outdated dependencies causing deprecation warnings in Jenkins build (Node.js 24 + npm 11) · Issue #3043 · exceljs/exceljs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/3043\"},{\"title\":\"The npm Deprecated Warning Nobody Reads (But Claude Does) - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/ji_ai/the-npm-deprecated-warning-nobody-reads-but-claude-does-1nh4\"},{\"title\":\"`loglevel=error` doesn't supress warnings, such as `WARN deprecated` and ` WARN Issues with peer dependencies found`. · Issue #4343 · pnpm/pnpm\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/issues/4343\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's information about handling npm deprecation warnings, suppressing logs, and managing transitive dependencies:\n\n## Suppressing npm Deprecation Warnings\n\nTo remove deprecated warnings, you can add the `--loglevel=error` option when running npm install, which will print only error messages when installing your dependencies. However, the suppression differs between categories: use `--loglevel=error` for npm install-time package warnings.\n\n## Understanding Transitive Dependencies\n\nMost deprecation warnings come from transitive dependencies. Updating direct dependencies with npm update only nudges within semver ranges and almost never clears transitive warnings. The correct approach is to identify the parent dependency with npm ls, then bump the parent's major version.\n\n## Best Practices for CI/CD\n\nIf you've reviewed the warnings and confirmed they're harmless, suppress them in CI to keep output readable. npm ci should complete without deprecation warnings from transitive dependencies.\n\n## Addressing Deprecated Dependencies\n\nRather than just suppressing warnings, for larger projects, consider integrating tools like Snyk, GitHub Dependabot, or Renovate into your CI/CD pipeline to automatically detect outdated/deprecated packages and even create pull requests for upgrades.\n\nThe key takeaway is that while you can suppress these warnings for CI/CD readability, the best practice is to actively address the underlying deprecated dependencies rather than just masking them.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
