[2026-07-19T12:31:39.325Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"git interpret-trailers \"last paragraph\" trailer block documentation blank line\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Git - git-interpret-trailers Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://git-scm.com/docs/git-interpret-trailers\"},{\"title\":\"git-interpret-trailers(1)\",\"url\":\"https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-interpret-trailers.html\"},{\"title\":\"htmldocs/git-interpret-trailers.html at gh-pages · git/htmldocs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/git/htmldocs/blob/gh-pages/git-interpret-trailers.html\"},{\"title\":\"htmldocs/git-interpret-trailers.adoc at gh-pages · git/htmldocs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/git/htmldocs/blob/gh-pages/git-interpret-trailers.adoc\"},{\"title\":\"git/trailer.h at master · git/git\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/git/git/blob/master/trailer.h\"},{\"title\":\"git-interpret-trailers(1) — Arch manual pages\",\"url\":\"https://man.archlinux.org/man/git-interpret-trailers.1.en\"},{\"title\":\"git-htmldocs/git-interpret-trailers.adoc at master · gitster/git-htmldocs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gitster/git-htmldocs/blob/master/git-interpret-trailers.adoc\"},{\"title\":\"git-interpret-trailers(1) — git-man — Debian testing — Debian Manpages\",\"url\":\"https://manpages.debian.org/testing/git-man/git-interpret-trailers.1.en.html\"},{\"title\":\"git-interpret-trailers - man pages section 1: User Commands\",\"url\":\"https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E86824_01/html/E54763/git-interpret-trailers-1.html\"},{\"title\":\"Understanding Git Commit Trailers • Simone Gigante Gassó\",\"url\":\"https://www.simonegigante.com/posts/commit-trailers/\"}]\n\nHere are the search results for the git interpret-trailers documentation regarding the trailer block, blank lines, and the last paragraph:\n\n## Key Documentation Points\n\n**Trailer Block Requirements:**\n\nExisting trailers are extracted from the input by looking for a group of one or more lines that (i) is all trailers, or (ii) contains at least one Git-generated or user-configured trailer and consists of at least 25% trailers.\n\n**Blank Line Requirements:**\n\nThe group must be preceded by one or more empty (or whitespace-only) lines. Additionally, the group must either be at the end of the input or be the last non-whitespace lines before a line that starts with --- (followed by a space or the end of the line).\n\n**Blank Line Addition for New Trailers:**\n\nA blank line will be added before the new trailer if there isn't one already.\n\nThese requirements ensure that git interpret-trailers can reliably identify and parse the trailer block at the end of commit messages while maintaining proper formatting with blank lines for separation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
