[2026-07-19T12:32:05.777Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"\"@vscode/vsce\" glob 10.5.0 deprecation warning dependency\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Clarification on deprecation notice for 10.5.0 and 11.1.0 · Issue #644 · isaacs/node-glob\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/isaacs/node-glob/issues/644\"},{\"title\":\"Update dependencies to support glob@10.5.0+ for security fix · Issue #15910 · jestjs/jest\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jestjs/jest/issues/15910\"},{\"title\":\"Deprecated glob@10.5.0 warning during npm install (via rimraf) · Issue #18327 · google-gemini/gemini-cli\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/18327\"},{\"title\":\"vsce - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/vsce\"},{\"title\":\"Deprecation warning during command line installation of VS Code extensions · Issue #133062 · microsoft/vscode\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/133062\"},{\"title\":\"Deprecation warning about use of Buffer() when installing an extension · Issue #202810 · microsoft/vscode\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/202810\"},{\"title\":\"Upgrade glob version? · Issue #267530 · microsoft/vscode\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/267530\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about the deprecation warning related to glob version 10.5.0:\n\nAll versions excluding 12.x and 13.x are deprecated with the message stating that \"Old versions of glob are not supported, and contain widely publicized security vulnerabilities, which have been fixed in the current version.\" This includes the 10.5.0 and 11.1.0 releases with patches for CVE-2025-64756.\n\nThe issue is that the earliest fixed version is glob@10.5.0, but this version itself is still marked as deprecated. The deprecation warning you're seeing when using @vscode/vsce likely comes from a transitive dependency that includes glob 10.5.0 in its dependency chain. To resolve the warning, the dependency chains would need to be updated to use newer versions of glob (version 12.x or 13.x).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
