[2026-07-19T12:32:17.304Z] [INFO]         "content": "# Summary of Issue #644\n\n**Why are 10.5.0 and 11.1.0 deprecated despite containing CVE-2025-64756 fixes?**\n\nThe issue raises a contradiction: versions 10.5.0 and 11.1.0 were patched to address CVE-2025-64756, yet they still receive a deprecation notice stating that \"Old versions of glob...contain widely publicized security vulnerabilities.\" The user questions whether these specific patched versions truly harbor unpatched vulnerabilities.\n\n**isaacs' response/policy:**\n\nThe webpage content provided shows only the issue description itself—no response from isaacs is included. The issue remains open with the status \"Closed\" shown in the interface, but actual maintainer commentary is absent from this excerpt.\n\n**Which versions are not deprecated?**\n\nAccording to the deprecation message, only versions 12.x and 13.x are excluded from the deprecation notice, meaning they remain supported and not deprecated.\n\nThe core question appears unresolved within the visible content: whether versions 10.5.0 and 11.1.0, despite their security patches, should retain the deprecation warning."
