[2026-07-19T12:32:57.551Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"commitlint trailer validation rule \"signed-off-by\" gitlint conventional commits footer parser\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"\\\"trailer-exists\\\" rule not recognized as a valid rule · Issue #3033 · conventional-changelog/commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/conventional-changelog/commitlint/issues/3033\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - conventionalcommit/commitlint: commitlint checks if your commit messages meets the conventional commit format · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/conventionalcommit/commitlint\"},{\"title\":\"Conventional Commits\",\"url\":\"https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/\"},{\"title\":\"Check for signed-off-by doesn't ignore comments · Issue #1809 · conventional-changelog/commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/conventional-changelog/commitlint/issues/1809\"},{\"title\":\"Rules | commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://commitlint.js.org/reference/rules.html\"},{\"title\":\"fix(rules): ignore comments in `signed-off-by` by bajtos · Pull Request #2098 · conventional-changelog/commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/conventional-changelog/commitlint/pull/2098\"},{\"title\":\"commitlint/config-conventional\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@commitlint/config-conventional\"},{\"title\":\"commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://commitlint.js.org/\"},{\"title\":\"commitlint/@commitlint/rules/src/trailer-exists.ts at master · conventional-changelog/commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/conventional-changelog/commitlint/blob/master/@commitlint/rules/src/trailer-exists.ts\"},{\"title\":\"Apply conventional commit style on your project with commitlint\",\"url\":\"https://blog.tericcabrel.com/apply-conventional-commit-style-on-your-project-with-commitlint/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding commitlint validation rules and the \"signed-off-by\" trailer:\n\n## Supported Rules in commitlint\n\nThe supported rule names in commitlint include: body-case, body-empty, body-leading-blank, body-max-length, body-max-line-length, body-min-length, footer-empty, footer-leading-blank, footer-max-length, footer-max-line-length, footer-min-length, header-case, header-full-stop, header-max-length, header-min-length, references-empty, scope-case, scope-empty, scope-enum, scope-max-length, scope-min-length, signed-off-by, subject-case, subject-empty, subject-full-stop, subject-max-length, subject-min-length, type-case, type-empty, type-enum, type-max-length, type-min-length.\n\n## The \"signed-off-by\" Rule\n\nThe `signed-off-by` rule is a built-in commitlint rule used to enforce that commit messages contain a \"Signed-off-by\" trailer. The `signed-off-by` rule ignores lines starting with `#`, which are comments added by `git commit` at the end of the commit message template.\n\n## Conventional Commits Footer Format\n\nRegarding how footers are structured in conventional commits: Each footer must consist of a word token, followed by either a `: ` or ` # ` separator, followed by a string value, with the footer's token using `-` in place of whitespace characters, e.g., Acked-by. This follows the git trailer convention.\n\nNote: A `trailer-exists` rule has been documented but is not currently recognized as a valid rule name by commitlint, despite appearing in documentation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
