[2026-07-19T12:35:29.280Z] [INFO]         "content": "Web search results for query: \"npm cli issue \"suppress deprecation warnings\" transitive dependencies feature request npm/cli\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Suppress specific warnings · Issue #40940 · nodejs/node\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/40940\"},{\"title\":\"An option for not showing deprecation warnings for transitive dependencies? · Issue #9720 · pnpm/pnpm\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/issues/9720\"},{\"title\":\"Warnings and dependencies in the Node.js and npm world - Office Add-ins | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/dev/add-ins/overview/npm-warnings-advice\"},{\"title\":\"[Change] Make deprecation notices less scary · Issue #7633 · npm/cli\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/npm/cli/issues/7633\"},{\"title\":\"Preventing pnpm from displaying too many deprecation warnings · Issue #4306 · pnpm/pnpm\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/issues/4306\"},{\"title\":\"How to handle npm WARN deprecated messages when installing dependencies | sebhastian\",\"url\":\"https://sebhastian.com/npm-warn-deprecated/\"},{\"title\":\"suppress-warnings - npm\",\"url\":\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/suppress-warnings\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here are the key findings related to suppressing deprecation warnings for transitive dependencies in npm:\n\n## npm/cli Issue\n\nThe default behavior of npm is to warn about every deprecated packages in the entire installation, regardless of how deep it is inside of the dependency tree. A relevant issue on npm/cli is GitHub issue #7633, which addresses the need to make deprecation notices less scary. The issue mentions packages used by eslint that the maintainer has no ability to change, yet users have been getting inundated with complaints about deprecation warnings even though these packages work fine.\n\n## Current Workarounds\n\nOne option to suppress deprecation warnings is to add the --loglevel=error option when running npm install, which will print only error messages. Additionally, there is the option to suppress all deprecation warnings with --no-deprecation, but this could lead to missing other deprecations that do impact you.\n\n## Similar Feature Requests\n\nA related feature request exists in the pnpm project (issue #9720) where users requested a way to disable these warnings for devDependencies or to specify a package for which its transitive dependencies would also be \"allowed\".\n\nThis is clearly a known pain point in the npm ecosystem, with multiple package managers receiving similar feature requests for more granular control over deprecation warning suppression.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
