[2026-07-19T12:35:30.879Z] [INFO]         "content": "# npm Config: Loglevel Values and Output Control\n\n## Loglevel Values\n\nAccording to npm documentation, the `loglevel` config supports these values:\n\n**\"silent\", \"error\", \"warn\", \"notice\", \"http\", \"info\", \"verbose\", or \"silly\"**\n\nThe default is set to \"notice\". The documentation explains that \"any logs of a higher level than the setting are shown,\" meaning lower levels get filtered out.\n\n## Key Output Control Options\n\n**Foreground Scripts**: The `foreground-scripts` setting runs build scripts in the main process, sharing input/output/error streams. This defaults to `false` except during `npm pack` or `npm publish`. The trade-off is slower, noisier installations but better debugging visibility.\n\n**Silent Mode**: You can achieve silent output through multiple methods:\n- Setting `--loglevel silent`\n- Using the `-s` shorthand flag\n- Using `--silent` (which maps to the same setting)\n\n**Error and Warning Suppression**: The `loglevel` configuration directly controls warning visibility—set it to \"error\" to suppress warnings, or to \"silent\" to eliminate all output except critical issues.\n\nAll logs are written to a debug file regardless of loglevel setting, with the file path displayed if command execution fails."
