[2026-07-19T12:51:39.230Z] [INFO]           "command": "gh pr edit 797 --repo link-assistant/formal-ai --title \"Fix two CI false positives failing the default branch\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFixes #796.\n\nTwo independent root causes — both **false positives** — landed on merge commit `12a4b34e` and together produced what looked like one broad CI collapse.\n\nFull investigation, logs and evidence: [`dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/`](dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/).\n\n## Root cause A — version-pinned npm deprecation allowlist\n\nEvery job that installs Node dependencies failed with exit code 1 *after* npm itself succeeded (`added 587 packages in 21s`):\n\n```\nUnexpected npm stderr; update dependencies or explicitly classify the diagnostic:\nnpm warn deprecated glob@10.5.0: Old versions of glob are not supported, ...\n##[error]Process completed with exit code 1.\n```\n\n`scripts/install-node-dependencies.sh` allowlisted reviewed upstream deprecations by **exact `name@version`** (`*\"npm warn deprecated glob@7.2.3:\"*`). Transitive versions float without any change on our side; when `archiver-utils` resolved `glob` to `10.5.0` the warning no longer matched, fell through to the \"unexpected\" bucket, and failed the `.vsix` packaging job **and all four desktop builds**.\n\n**Corrected attribution.** The old allowlist implied `glob` came from electron-builder or vsce. Verified against the committed lockfiles, it does not:\n\n```\n@link-assistant/web-capture@^1.10.10 -> archiver@7.0.1\n  -> archiver-utils@5.0.2 (glob ^10.0.0) -> glob@10.5.0\n```\n\n`@vscode/vsce@3.9.2` already uses `glob ^13.0.6`; electron-builder pulls only `glob@7.2.3`. Upstream deprecated every glob below 12.x — including the releases that *fix* CVE-2025-64756 ([isaacs/node-glob#644](https://github.com/isaacs/node-glob/issues/644)) — so the warning is unavoidable noise, not an actionable vulnerability.\n\n**Fix.** Reviewed deprecations are matched by **package name only**, with accurate per-package tracking URLs. Unreviewed diagnostics still fail the build, so the check keeps its value.\n\n## Root cause B — desktop builds\n\nNot independent: all `Build <platform>` jobs and the `vscode` job fail through the same shared script, so fix A resolves them all.\n\n## Root cause C — a blank line hides a git trailer\n\nAuto Release failed immediately after computing version `0.299.0`:\n\n```\nError recording self-hosting release metric: commit 59650f2b...\nmust record both Formal-AI-Session and Formal-AI-Evidence\n```\n\n**The commit records both.** But a blank line sits between them. Per [git-interpret-trailers](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-interpret-trailers), trailers are extracted from *one* group that *\"must either be at the end of the input or be the last non-whitespace lines before a line that starts with `---`.\"* The blank line splits them into two paragraphs, so `%(trailers:key=Formal-AI-Session)` returned nothing — a **false negative** in trailer detection escalating into a failed release.\n\n**Fix.** `trailer_values` now scans the full commit body for `Key: value` lines, case-insensitively. Placement no longer decides whether a compliant commit is recognised.\n\n## How to reproduce\n\n```bash\n# Root cause C, in a clean fixture:\ngit commit -m \"subject\n\nFormal-AI-Session: ses_abc\n\nFormal-AI-Evidence: docs/e.log\"\ngit show -s '--format=%(trailers:key=Formal-AI-Session,valueonly)' HEAD   # -> empty\n```\n\n## Tests\n\n- `tests/unit/ci-cd/issue_796.rs` — five tests driving the **real script** against a fake `npm`: the floated `glob@10.5.0` line no longer fails; unreviewed diagnostics still do; scoped names keep their scope; verbose mode exists and is off by default; the allowlist may not contain a pinned version.\n- `tests/unit/specification/self_hosting_metric.rs` — a commit whose trailers are separated by a blank line is attributed correctly.\n\nBoth suites were **confirmed to fail against the pre-fix scripts** and pass after; the trailer test reproduces the production error string verbatim. `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features` and `cargo fmt --check` are clean; all 111 `ci_cd::` tests pass, including the pre-existing `issue_730` assertions on the modified script.\n\n## Debug output\n\n`INSTALL_NODE_DEPENDENCIES_VERBOSE=1` traces every classification decision, so an unexpected diagnostic can be diagnosed from CI logs without a local reproduction. **Off by default**, enforced by test.\n\n## Scope notes\n\n- The two `skipped` Desktop Release runs listed in the issue are **benign** — `workflow_run` runs whose `resolve` job found no desktop assets were needed. No change required.\n- Verified both defective patterns exist in exactly one place each, and that every workflow npm install routes through the shared script, so the fixes apply repo-wide.\n- The template comparison (issue requirement) is in [`template-gap-analysis.md`](dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/template-gap-analysis.md). It found six real gaps (missing `Cargo.lock` guard job, no post-publish smoke test, no secrets scanning, no fresh-merge simulation, non-resilient Buildx setup, file-size check excluding `.yml`/`.md`) plus five fixes this repo has that the templates lack. Those are **deliberately not bundled here** — they are unrelated to the #796 failures and each deserves separate review. Recommended landing order is documented in that file.\nEOF\n)\" && echo \"PR UPDATED\"",
