[2026-07-19T12:53:39.058Z] [INFO]         "text": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. **Primary Request and Intent:**\n\n   The user (via an AI-issue-solver harness) gave a single directive to solve https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/796 on branch `issue-796-9da6718935fa` in `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1784464066233`, updating existing PR #797. Explicit requirements:\n   - \"Download all logs and collect data related about the issue to this repository, and compile that data into the ./dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797 folder.\"\n   - \"Use the collected evidence to do a deep analysis (search online for additional facts and data), reconstruct the timeline/sequence of events, list each and every requirement from the issue, find the root cause of each problem, and propose possible solutions and solution plans for each requirement. Also check online for known existing components/libraries that solve a similar problem or can help.\"\n   - \"If there is not enough data to find the actual root cause, add debug output and a verbose mode (if not already present) so the root cause can be found on the next iteration. Keep the default state switched off.\"\n   - \"If the issue is related to another repository/project, report issues on GitHub for that project when possible. Each report must contain reproducible examples, workarounds, and suggestions for fixing the issue in code.\"\n   - \"Double-check that the requirements are fully applied to the entire codebase: if an issue exists in multiple places, apply it in all of them.\"\n   - Embedded guidelines: create reproducing test BEFORE the fix; commit atomic steps; run local CI checks before pushing; push only to `issue-796-9da6718935fa`; use `gh pr edit` to update PR 797; run `gh pr ready 797` when finished; merge default branch into PR branch; verify clean working tree; check all CI passing; update version/release trigger.\n\n   The GitHub issue itself (\"Check for all false positives, false negatives, warnings and errors in CI/CD and fix them all\") additionally required comparing all files against three templates (link-foundation rust-/js-/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template), following https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/main/docs/CI-CD-BEST-PRACTICES.md, reporting issues upstream in the templates if the same problem exists there, and doing everything in the single PR.\n\n2. **Key Technical Concepts:**\n   - GitHub Actions workflows (`release.yml` 1565 L, `desktop-release.yml` 649 L), `gh` CLI log retrieval\n   - npm stderr diagnostics: `npm warn deprecated` goes to stderr but npm exits 0; `loglevel` values; no per-package/transitive suppression exists (npm/cli#7633)\n   - glob deprecation: all versions below 12.x deprecated including 10.5.0/11.1.0 which are themselves the CVE-2025-64756 patches (isaacs/node-glob#644)\n   - npm lockfile dependency-chain tracing via `packages` map in package-lock.json\n   - git trailer semantics: `git interpret-trailers` / `%(trailers:key=...)` only parses the LAST paragraph; the group \"must either be at the end of the input or be the last non-whitespace lines before a line that starts with `---`\"; 25% heuristic\n   - Rust integration test layout: `tests/unit/mod.rs` with `#[path = \"../../../scripts/*.rs\"] mod ...` including scripts as modules\n   - changelog.d fragment convention with `---\\nbump: patch\\n---` frontmatter; `version-and-commit.rs` auto-bumps from fragments (no manual version edit needed)\n   - Bash parameter expansion for scoped npm package names\n\n3. **Files and Code Sections:**\n\n   - **`scripts/install-node-dependencies.sh`** (MODIFIED — root cause A fix)\n     - Why: shared by every Node-installing CI job (vsix packaging + all 4 desktop builds). Original classified deprecations by exact `name@version` in a bash `case`, e.g. `*\"npm warn deprecated glob@7.2.3:\"*`. When `archiver-utils` floated glob to `10.5.0`, it fell through to the \"unexpected\" bucket and exited 1 despite npm succeeding.\n     - Rewritten with a `package|title|url` allowlist:\n     ```bash\n     # \"<package>|<title>|<tracking url>\". One entry per reviewed package name.\n     #\n     # glob is pulled in by two independent chains, so it is attributed to the one\n     # we can actually act on: @link-assistant/web-capture -> archiver@7.0.1 ->\n     # archiver-utils@5.0.2 -> glob@10.5.0. (electron-builder separately pulls\n     # glob@7.2.3.) Upstream deprecated every glob below 12.x, including the very\n     # releases that fix CVE-2025-64756, so the warning is unavoidable noise rather\n     # than an actionable vulnerability -- see isaacs/node-glob#644.\n     reviewed_deprecations=(\n       \"inflight|electron-builder upstream deprecation|https://github.com/electron-userland/electron-builder/issues/10016\"\n       \"rimraf|electron-builder upstream deprecation|https://github.com/electron-userland/electron-builder/issues/10016\"\n       \"boolean|electron-builder upstream deprecation|https://github.com/electron-userland/electron-builder/issues/10016\"\n       \"lodash.isequal|electron-builder upstream deprecation|https://github.com/electron-userland/electron-builder/issues/10016\"\n       \"prebuild-install|vsce upstream deprecation|https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-vsce/issues/1290\"\n       \"whatwg-encoding|vsce upstream deprecation|https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-vsce/issues/1290\"\n       \"glob|archiver/electron-builder upstream deprecation|https://github.com/isaacs/node-glob/issues/644\"\n     )\n     ```\n     - Name extraction (after fixing my own bash bug):\n     ```bash\n     deprecated_package_name() {\n       local line=\"$1\" spec name\n       spec=\"${line#*npm warn deprecated }\"\n       spec=\"${spec%%:*}\"\n       # Strip the trailing @version. Removing the *last* '@' preserves a leading\n       # @scope, so \"@scope/pkg@1.2.3\" yields \"@scope/pkg\" and \"glob@10.5.0\" yields\n       # \"glob\". Guard the case where npm printed no version at all.\n       name=\"${spec%@*}\"\n       printf '%s' \"${name:-$spec}\"\n     }\n     ```\n     - Classification loop:\n     ```bash\n     while IFS= read -r line; do\n       case \"$line\" in\n         \"\") continue ;;\n         *\"npm warn deprecated \"*)\n           package=\"$(deprecated_package_name \"$line\")\"\n           classified=0\n           for entry in \"${reviewed_deprecations[@]}\"; do\n             if [[ \"${entry%%|*}\" == \"$package\" ]]; then\n               rest=\"${entry#*|}\"\n               trace \"classified '$package' as ${rest%%|*}\"\n               echo \"::notice title=${rest%%|*}::${line#npm warn } See ${rest#*|}\"\n               classified=1\n               break\n             fi\n           done\n           if [[ \"$classified\" == \"0\" ]]; then\n             trace \"deprecation for '$package' is not on the reviewed allowlist\"\n             printf '%s\\n' \"$line\" >>\"$unexpected\"\n           fi\n           ;;\n         *) trace \"unrecognized diagnostic: $line\"; printf '%s\\n' \"$line\" >>\"$unexpected\" ;;\n       esac\n     done <\"$stderr_log\"\n     ```\n     - Verbose mode (default OFF, per user requirement):\n     ```bash\n     verbose=\"${INSTALL_NODE_DEPENDENCIES_VERBOSE:-0}\"\n     trace() {\n       [[ \"$verbose\" == \"1\" ]] || return 0\n       printf 'install-node-dependencies: %s\\n' \"$*\" >&2\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`scripts/self-hosting-metric.rs`** (MODIFIED — root cause C fix, `trailer_values` at ~line 149)\n     - Why: `version-and-commit.rs` calls `record_self_hosting_release` and `exit(1)`s on error, so a mis-parsed trailer fails the whole Auto Release job.\n     - Was: `let format = format!(\"%(trailers:key={key},valueonly,separator=%x1f)\");`\n     - Now:\n     ```rust\n     /// Collects `key: value` trailers from a commit message.\n     ///\n     /// This deliberately scans the whole commit body instead of using git's\n     /// `%(trailers:key=...)` placeholder. Git only recognises the *last* paragraph\n     /// of a message as the trailer block, so a blank line between two trailers\n     /// makes every trailer above it invisible. Release commit\n     /// 59650f2b45ebebf29ed67d33c9a19c1e82e7c003 separated its `Formal-AI-Session`\n     /// and `Formal-AI-Evidence` trailers with a blank line, git reported only the\n     /// evidence trailer, and the resulting \"must record both\" error failed the\n     /// whole Auto Release job (issue #796).\n     fn trailer_values(repo: &Path, commit: &str, key: &str) -> Result<Vec<String>, String> {\n         let body = git(repo, &[\"show\", \"-s\", \"--format=%B\", commit])?;\n         let prefix = format!(\"{key}:\");\n         Ok(body\n             .lines()\n             .filter_map(|line| {\n                 let line = line.trim();\n                 // Trailer keys are case-insensitive per `git interpret-trailers`.\n                 line.get(..prefix.len())\n                     .filter(|candidate| candidate.eq_ignore_ascii_case(&prefix))\n                     .map(|_| line[prefix.len()..].trim())\n             })\n             .filter(|value| !value.is_empty())\n             .map(str::to_owned)\n             .collect())\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`tests/unit/ci-cd/issue_796.rs`** (CREATED — 5 tests) — drives the real script against a fake `npm` written into a temp sandbox dir prepended to PATH. Tests: `reviewed_deprecations_are_matched_by_package_name_not_pinned_version` (uses the exact glob@10.5.0 line from run 29681451142), `unreviewed_diagnostics_still_fail_the_build`, `scoped_package_names_are_parsed_without_losing_the_scope`, `verbose_tracing_exists_and_is_off_by_default`, `the_classifier_does_not_pin_versions_in_its_allowlist` (asserts the allowlist block contains no `@`).\n\n   - **`tests/unit/ci-cd/mod.rs`** (MODIFIED) — added `mod issue_796;` after `mod issue_742;`\n\n   - **`tests/unit/specification/self_hosting_metric.rs`** (MODIFIED) — added before `release_pipeline_and_ledger_remain_pinned_to_the_metric`:\n     ```rust\n     /// Regression for issue #796: release commit 59650f2b separated its two\n     /// trailers with a blank line. ...\n     #[test]\n     fn trailers_are_recognized_even_when_separated_by_blank_lines() {\n         let repo = fixture_repo();\n         ...\n         commit(&repo, \"formal ai change\\n\\nFormal-AI-Session: spaced-session\\n\\nFormal-AI-Evidence: docs/evidence/session.txt\");\n         let measurement = metric_script::measure(&repo, \"v1.0.0\", \"HEAD\").expect(\"measurement must succeed\");\n         assert_eq!(measurement.self_authored_commits, 1, \"a blank line between trailers must not hide the session trailer\");\n         fs::remove_dir_all(repo).expect(\"fixture directory must be removed\");\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`changelog.d/20260719_130000_issue_796_ci_false_positives.md`** (CREATED) — `bump: patch`, with `### Fixed` entries for both root causes and `### Added` for the verbose env var.\n\n   - **`dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/`** (CREATED) — `README.md` (index table + summary), `timeline-and-root-cause.md` (full timeline, 3 root causes, R1–R9 requirement table, upstream reports list, regression coverage), `template-gap-analysis.md`, `online-research.md`; plus `ci-logs/run-{29680908415,29681451142,29686858791,29686071628}.log` and `raw/` (issue/PR/run JSON, `commit-59650f2b-message.txt`, `glob-dependency-chain.txt`, `main-runs.json`).\n\n   - **`.gitkeep`** — DELETED (its own content stated \"This file will be removed when the task is complete\").\n\n4. **Errors and fixes:**\n\n   - **My own bash bug:** First version of `deprecated_package_name` used `printf '%s' \"@${spec:1%@*}\"` — invalid bash mixing substring and suffix-removal expansion. Fixed by using `name=\"${spec%@*}\"; printf '%s' \"${name:-$spec}\"`, which correctly yields `@scope/pkg` for scoped and `glob` for unscoped, guarding the no-version case. Verified with a fake-npm harness.\n\n   - **Mis-attribution I introduced and self-corrected:** My initial allowlist put `glob` under `electron_builder_deprecations`, which would have emitted a misleading \"electron-builder upstream deprecation\" annotation. The research agent flagged that glob@10.5.0 actually comes from `@link-assistant/web-capture → archiver → archiver-utils`. I **independently verified this myself** by parsing both `vscode/package-lock.json` and `desktop/package-lock.json` with python3 before acting, confirming `archiver-utils 5.0.2 -> glob ^10.0.0`, `glob 10.5.0`, and `@link-assistant/web-capture -> archiver ^7.0.1`. Then restructured the allowlist to a `package|title|url` form with the correct isaacs/node-glob#644 attribution.\n\n   - **Background job left repo in reverted state:** While proving red→green I ran `git checkout scripts/self-hosting-metric.rs` in a background job; a system-reminder showed the file with the OLD `trailer_values`. I waited for the job's `RESTORED` marker and confirmed with `grep -c \"scans the whole commit body\"` → 1 before committing.\n\n   No user feedback/corrections were received during the session — there was only one genuine user turn (the initial directive). All subsequent inputs were automated background-task notifications and system reminders.\n\n5. **Problem Solving:**\n\n   Diagnosed the issue's \"one broad CI collapse\" as **two independent root causes** on the same commit `12a4b34e`, both **false positives**:\n   - **A/B:** version-pinned npm deprecation allowlist → failed the `.vsix` job and all 4 desktop builds (B is not a separate defect; all route through the same shared script, which is why the fix belongs there).\n   - **C:** blank-line-split git trailers → false negative in trailer detection escalating into a hard Auto Release failure.\n   - Also determined the two \"skipped\" Desktop Release runs listed in the issue are **benign**, not defects (workflow_run-triggered, resolve job found no desktop assets needed).\n\n   Both bugs were reproduced independently (a case-statement simulation and a clean git fixture repo) before fixing, and both regression suites were confirmed to **fail against the pre-fix scripts** — the trailer test reproducing the production error string verbatim (\"must record both Formal-AI-Session and Formal-AI-Evidence\").\n\n   Verified R6 by grepping: only one `%(trailers` call site, no npm install in workflows outside the shared script, only one version-pinned allowlist.\n\n   All checks pass: `cargo fmt --check` clean, `bash -n` ok, `cargo test --test unit ci_cd::` → 111 passed (including pre-existing `issue_730` assertions on the modified script), `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features` clean. Committed as a5b9d597 and pushed.\n\n6. **All user messages:**\n   - The single genuine user message was the initial task directive (reproduced in full detail in section 1 above): solve issue #796 on branch `issue-796-9da6718935fa`, compile logs/data into `./dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797`, do deep analysis with online research, reconstruct the timeline, list every requirement, find root causes, propose solutions, check for existing components/libraries, add verbose/debug output with **default state switched off** if data is insufficient, report issues to other GitHub projects when the issue belongs to them (with reproducible examples, workarounds, and code fix suggestions), and \"Double-check that the requirements are fully applied to the entire codebase: if an issue exists in multiple places, apply it in all of them.\" Plus the embedded workflow guidelines (push only to `issue-796-9da6718935fa`, update PR 797 rather than creating a new one, run `gh pr ready 797` when finished, merge default branch in, verify CI passing, reproduce before fixing).\n   - The final user message instructed: respond with TEXT ONLY, no tool calls, producing this analysis and summary.\n\n   No security-relevant constraints or prohibited operations were stated beyond the branch restriction (push only to `issue-796-9da6718935fa`, respect branch protections, use PRs rather than direct merges to main/master).\n\n7. **Pending Tasks:**\n   - Update PR #797 title and description via `gh pr edit` (currently \"[WIP] Check for all false positives...\" with an auto-generated placeholder body)\n   - Run `gh pr ready 797` to mark it ready\n   - File the 4 identified upstream reports (issue explicitly requires this): (1) `@link-assistant/web-capture` — bump `archiver` / override glob to 13.x to clear glob@10.5.0 at source; (2) all three link-foundation templates — Rust template `release.yml` has no top-level `permissions:` block; (3) all three templates — `cargo install rust-script` unretried; (4) rust/python templates — `codecov/codecov-action` on `@v5`/`@v4` (v4 deprecated). Each report must include reproducible examples, workarounds, and code fix suggestions.\n   - Merge `main` into the PR branch\n   - Verify CI passes on the pushed branch (download fresh logs, confirm timestamps/SHA are after commit a5b9d597)\n   - Optionally act on the template-gap follow-ups documented in `template-gap-analysis.md` §4 (Cargo.lock guard job, post-publish smoke test, resilient buildx, `defaults.run.shell: bash` + `set -euo pipefail` in release.yml, secrets scanning, fresh-merge simulation) — these were deliberately scoped OUT of this PR as separate reviewable changes\n\n8. **Current Work:**\n\n   Immediately before the summary request, I had completed the fix-and-verify cycle and committed/pushed. The last two actions were:\n   ```\n   git add -A && git rm --cached .gitkeep -q; rm -f .gitkeep; git add -A && git commit -q -F - <<'EOF'\n   Fix two CI false positives failing the default branch\n   ...\n   EOF\n   → COMMITTED\n   ```\n   and\n   ```\n   git push -u origin issue-796-9da6718935fa\n   → d9405736..a5b9d597  issue-796-9da6718935fa -> issue-796-9da6718935fa\n   ```\n   Working tree is clean; commit a5b9d597 is on the remote branch. The code fixes, regression tests, changelog fragment, and all four analysis documents plus raw evidence are committed.\n\n9. **Optional Next Step:**\n\n   Update the PR metadata and mark it ready, which the user's directive explicitly requires: \"When you update existing pr 797, use gh pr edit to modify title and description\" and \"When you finish implementation, use gh pr ready 797.\" Concretely: replace the placeholder body with the two root causes, the reproduction/verification evidence (both suites confirmed failing pre-fix, trailer test reproducing the production error string verbatim), the R1–R9 requirement table from `timeline-and-root-cause.md`, and a pointer to `dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/`. Then file the four upstream issues, merge `main` into the branch, and verify CI on the pushed commit.\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/box/.claude/projects/-tmp-gh-issue-solver-1784464066233/b7b0a7df-eaec-4996-8eac-65c1201e46d2.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."
