[2026-07-19T12:55:46.315Z] [INFO]           "command": "cd /tmp && BODY=\"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n`.github/workflows/release.yml` has **no top-level `permissions:` block**. The file goes straight from `on:` to `concurrency:`, so every job inherits the repository's default `GITHUB_TOKEN` scope — which on many organisations is still read/write-all.\n\nThis matters more here than in an ordinary workflow: `release.yml` is the file that publishes packages, pushes tags and commits, and creates releases, so it is the highest-value token in the repository.\n\n## Reproducible check\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/contents/.github/workflows/release.yml --jq .content \\\n  | base64 -d | grep -n '^permissions:' || echo \"NONE\"\n# -> NONE\n```\n\nThen compare against the effective grant:\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/actions/permissions/workflow --jq .default_workflow_permissions\n# -> \"write\" on organisations that have not changed the default\n```\n\nAny workflow step — or any compromised third-party action, all of which float on mutable major tags here — then runs with write access to repository contents.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nAdd least-privilege at the top of the file and escalate per job only where needed:\n\n```diff\n on:\n   push:\n     branches: [main]\n\n+permissions:\n+  contents: read\n+\n concurrency:\n```\n\nThen, on the jobs that genuinely need more:\n\n```yaml\n  release:\n    permissions:\n      contents: write      # create tags/releases\n      id-token: write      # trusted publishing / attestations\n```\n\n`link-assistant/formal-ai` applies exactly this pattern (`release.yml:32-33`, with per-job escalation) and its release pipeline works unchanged.\n\n## Workaround\n\nOrganisation owners can set **Settings → Actions → Workflow permissions → Read repository contents** as the default, but that is repo-external configuration that a template consumer will not inherit when they generate a new project from this template. The fix belongs in the template so every generated repository is safe by default.\n\n## Scope\n\nFiled against all three pipeline templates (`rust-`, `js-`, `python-`); verified missing in each. Discovered while auditing CI/CD against these templates in link-assistant/formal-ai#796.\nEOF\n)\"; for r in rust js python; do gh issue create --repo \"link-foundation/$r-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template\" --title \"release.yml has no top-level permissions: block, so jobs inherit the default GITHUB_TOKEN scope\" --body \"$BODY\"; done",
