[2026-07-19T12:56:31.719Z] [INFO]           "command": "cd /tmp && gh issue create --repo link-foundation/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template --title \"codecov/codecov-action pinned to deprecated @v4 (current is v7)\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n`release.yml:244` uses `codecov/codecov-action@v4`. The current major is **v7.0.0** (released 2026-06-07), so the template is three majors behind.\n\nv4 is the last major built on the deprecated **bash uploader**, which Codecov has retired; v5+ use the Codecov CLI. Repositories generated from this template will keep emitting deprecation notices and are exposed to the uploader being switched off entirely.\n\n## Reproducible check\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/link-foundation/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/contents/.github/workflows/release.yml \\\n  --jq .content | base64 -d | grep -n 'codecov/codecov-action@'\n# 244:        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n\ngh api repos/codecov/codecov-action/releases/latest --jq .tag_name\n# v7.0.0\n```\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n```diff\n-        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n+        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v7\n```\n\nCheck the [v5 migration notes](https://github.com/codecov/codecov-action/releases) when bumping — the v4→v5 step renamed several inputs (notably `file` → `files`), so a straight tag bump can silently stop uploading if the old input name is still in use.\n\n## Workaround\n\nConsumers can override the version in their generated repository, but every newly generated project starts on the deprecated action, so the fix belongs in the template.\n\n## Related\n\nThe `rust-` template is on `@v5` — not deprecated, but also behind current; worth bumping in the same pass. `link-assistant/formal-ai` is on `@v7`. Found while auditing CI/CD against these templates in link-assistant/formal-ai#796.\nEOF\n)\"",
