[2026-07-19T12:57:32.452Z] [INFO]         "input": {
[2026-07-19T12:57:32.452Z] [INFO]           "command": "git add -A && git commit -q -F - <<'EOF' && git push -q origin issue-796-9da6718935fa && echo PUSHED\nRecord upstream reports and correct two analysis claims\n\nFiled six upstream issues for the gaps this audit found:\n\n- link-assistant/web-capture#144 (archiver@7 -> deprecated glob@10.5.0)\n- rust#97, js#104, python#33 (no top-level permissions: in release.yml)\n- rust#98 (cargo install rust-script unretried and unlocked)\n- python#34, rust#99 (outdated codecov/codecov-action)\n\nTwo corrections to the analysis, both from verifying against the actual\nupstream files rather than the earlier draft:\n\n- The rust-script gap exists in the Rust template only, not all three;\n  the js and python templates never invoke it. The report was filed\n  accordingly.\n- A concrete source fix exists for the glob chain: archiver@8.0.0 drops\n  archiver-utils entirely for readdir-glob@^3 (minimatch only), so no\n  glob remains in its tree. It requires node >= 18, noted upstream.\nEOF",
[2026-07-19T12:57:32.452Z] [INFO]           "description": "Commit doc corrections"
